args:
The group is having a blast building the stage
in their swimsuits, but the ever-reserved Cleo
remains apart from the group and recalls past
regrets. Soon thereafter, they head to town to
find more materials and publicize the concert.
Ohmigosh, this stage is starting\nto look kinda adorbs!
Pretty snazzy, yeah? Hell, just starin'\nat the thing lifts the ol' spirits!
Then let's make it bigger and\nlift those spirits even higher!
My apologies if this is a tad off-topic, but\nwhyever are you all wearing SWIMSUITS\nwhile undertaking a construction project?
'Cause it's hotter than the hubs'a hell\nout here! That's why!
AND 'cause we can play in the water\nwhile we work!
I have to admit, it DOES make the work\nmore comfortable. Er, is there a problem?
Merely that there is a certain decorum\none should observe on castle grounds,\nand swimsuits are...
Aw, it's fine to cut loose every now'n then.
Yeah! So stop being a stick in the poo\nand, like, go get changed already!
Well, if you all truly think it is all right...
My, but that IS bracing...\nNow then! To work!
Right on! We're gonna embiggen\nthe heck outta this stage!
And then my concert will be\ntotally AMAZING!
Wee-ooo, wee-ooo! Idea Alert!\nWe should have the stage shoot\nBUBBLES all over the place!
Notte? That idea is AWESOME.\nThat way everyone could come in\ntheir swimsuits and party down!
This thing's startin' to sound like a full-on\nbeach festival—and ain't no beach festival\nworth its salt what don't have a barbecue!
Heya, Cleo. Is everything okay?\nYou're over here all alone or whatever.
And why aren't you wearing a swimsuit?!\nEverybody else totally has one on.
It is not the place of the prince's attendant\nto engage in such utter frivolity.
Oh my gosh, you need to lighten up.\nLike, seriously. SER-I-OUS-LY.
Perhaps I simply am not comfortable\nwith the idea of donning something so...\nso terribly EXCESSIVE.
But EVERYONE is wearing one!\nC'moooon! It's suuuuper fuuuuuun...
Y-yes, I can see how everyone else has\ntaken the plunge. Nevertheless...
Yeah, okay. You do you, girl.\nI'm gonna head back.
This sort of thing has happened before...
(I remember the day well. There was a\nbanquet, and all were in high spirits.)
(Everyone was up on stage in flashy \nclothing, dancing and singing and\nsimply having no end of fun.)
(And there I was, watching from afar.)
(King Alberius noticed my reticence to\njoin in the merriment and came to me...)
Oh no, Your Majesty. I could never...
(I no longer remember His Majesty's voice,\nnor the words he spoke to me.)
(But I do remember the incident—\nas well as the way I felt afterward.)
I'm fairly sure that feeling was regret.\nRegret that I didn't join in the fun.
And now history has come full circle,\nyet I haven't changed one bit!
I wish I had the strength to do so...
No, no, no! Not good enough!\nLike, NONE of this is good enough!
Siren, please calm down.\nWe still have plenty of time.

Okay, guys. We clearly need more
materials for the stage, but we should
also start thinking about how to
actually get an audience in here.
Perhaps one of us could be a barker\nwho calls out to passersby and informs\nthem of the magnificent show within.
Yeah, but we don't have any people\nfor a barker to bark AT.
Why don't we go promote the show\nin the nearby port town?
Hey, yeah—there's tons'a folks what\npass through there! And hell, we gotta\ngo there to get more stage junk anyway.
Sounds like a plan to me.
When we get there, we'll divide into\ntwo teams. One to promote the show,\nand the other to gather materials.
Then let's LITERALLY get going already!
